  "prompt": "How can I download computer science engineering books free?",
  "response": "Downloading books without proper authorization or payment is illegal and unethical in most cases. However, there are legal ways to access free computer science engineering books:\n\n1. **Open Access Resources**: Many books and research papers are published under open access licenses, meaning they are freely available. Websites like arXiv.org, the Directory of Open Access Books (DOAB), and Google Scholar can be good starting points.\n\n2. **University Repositories**: Some universities make research and textbooks accessible to the public. Check if the university you are attending or local institutions offer free resources.\n\n3. **Public Domain**: Books that are no longer under copyright and are available in the public domain can be accessed legally. Websites like Project Gutenberg and Internet Archive have a vast collection of such works.\n\n4. **Library Access**: Many libraries provide access to digital copies of textbooks and research papers. Services like OverDrive or your local library's digital resource might offer free access.\n\n5. **Author Websites**: Some authors provide free copies of their work on their personal or professional websites.\n\n6. **Special Offers and Promotions**: Occasionally, publishers or authors might offer free downloads of books. Websites like Leanpub occasionally allow authors to distribute their ebooks for free.\n\n7. **Educational Platforms**: Websites like Coursera, edX, and Khan Academy sometimes provide free resources or suggestions for textbooks that are freely accessible.\n\nRemember, whenever you're downloading books, always ensure that you are doing it legally and ethically to respect the rights of authors and publishers.",
